extends ./_layout/_page.pug

block vars
  -
    var page = data.pages.index;

block contentFixedBefore

block contentStatic
  .p-contents-header
    .p-contents-header__in
      h1.p-contents-header__title
        |Smooth Scroll Manager
      p.p-contents-header__excerpt.js-smooth-item
        |It's a utility JavaScript asset
        br
        |that controls smooth scroll and showing elements with scroll event.
      .p-contents-header__btn.js-smooth-item(
        data-ratio-y = 0.15
        )
        a.c-button-border.js-scroll-item.js-hover(
          href = 'https://github.com/ykob/scroll-manager',
          target = '_blank'
          )
          span.c-button-border__label
            |view source
          span.c-button-border__line-v
          span.c-button-border__line-h

  .l-contents__in
    .p-local-navi
      .p-local-navi__item
        a.c-text-link-underline.js-anchor-link.js-hover(
          href = '#section1'
          )
          |Section 1 JAMESON
      .p-local-navi__item
        a.c-text-link-underline.js-anchor-link.js-hover(
          href = '#section2'
          )
          |Section 2 Grand Old Parr
      .p-local-navi__item
        a.c-text-link-underline.js-anchor-link.js-hover(
          href = '#section3'
          )
          |Section 3 BUSHMILLS

    .c-section#section1
      .c-section__image
        .c-section__image-in.js-smooth-item
          img.js-parallax-item(
            src = `${data.meta.path}/img/common/photo_jameson.jpg`,
            alt = "",
            )
      .c-section__content
        h2.c-section__head
          |JAMESON
        p
          |The John Jameson and Son Irish Whiskey company was formally established in 1810 when John Jameson and his son (also John Jameson) took ownership of the Bow Street Distillery in Dublin which had originally been built by his wife's cousins the Steins in 1780.
        .c-button-border.c-button-border--black.js-scroll-item.js-hover.js-open-modal
          span.c-button-border__label.c-button-border__label--black
            |Open Modal
          span.c-button-border__line-v.c-button-border__line-v--black
          span.c-button-border__line-h.c-button-border__line-h--black

    .c-section.c-section--reverse#section2
      .c-section__image
        .c-section__image-in.js-smooth-item
          img.js-parallax-item(
            src = `${data.meta.path}/img/common/photo_oldparr.jpg`,
            alt = "",
            )
      .c-section__content
        h2.c-section__head
          |Grand Old Parr
        p
          |Grand Old Parr (often simply just Old Parr) is a blended Scotch whisky named after the reputed oldest man in England. Launched in 1909, it is found in export markets such as Japan, Mexico, South America and in The United States of America and is no longer distributed in the United Kingdom.

    .c-section#section3
      .c-section__image
        .c-section__image-in.js-smooth-item
          img.js-parallax-item(
            src = `${data.meta.path}/img/common/photo_bushmills.jpg`,
            alt = "",
            )
      .c-section__content
        h2.c-section__head
          |BUSHMILLS
        p
          |The Old Bushmills Distillery is a distillery in Bushmills, County Antrim, Northern Ireland. As of December 2014, it was in the process of transitioning from ownership by Diageo plc to Jose Cuervo.

